Pprocedures that use small incisions and microscopic instruments to reduce eye pressure (IOP). MIGS can involve less tissue manipulation than traditional glaucoma surgeries, such as trabeculectomy or tube-shunt surgery. MIGS can be safer and have a faster recovery time than traditional surgery, but it may not lower IOP as much.
